A10 #musochat innertia, negative thinking, an overwhelming rejection (which happens over and over). It takes discipline and a clear mission.
A9 #musochat great personal relationships trump any social media blitz. Marketing in contemp. classical music is all about relationships.
A7 #musochat an advantage to creating a smaller, stable ensemble is you can tour. Artist fees via touring pays for our part-time ensemble.
@jmgerraughty We were lucky - doing well at a competition got us some gigs, and we continued booking on our own from there.
@jdgaby We have never been non-profit - simply a registered business with fiscal sponsorship.
A5 #musochat we started for-profit, paying musicians as an "always" not a sometimes. We use @FracturedAtlas to help raise $ for projects.
@jmgerraughty In smaller details yes, but in a larger scope no; I think our mission has remained unchanged since inception! #musochat
@jmgerraughty quite a bit, but it's usually well-planned for in advance so we have time to hire a great long-term replacement.
@jmgerraughty We approach this every year, signing a new member agreement, re-negotiating what we all want from the ensemble.
A2 #musochat you should also consider long-term investment or short-term project. Do you want to still play with your ensemble in 5 yrs?
A2 #musochat creating the ensemble has helped many of our members in their careers - but you must start with the right people/right mission.
A1 #musochat The City of Tomorrow, new music ensemble disguised as a wind quintet. Based in NYC/Boston/Memphis.
